20/05/2009
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Police have arrested a Romanian national suspected of terrorist activities, Romanian media reported on Tuesday (May 19th). 
Hungarian authorities refuse to reveal the suspect's identity, but described him as part of a far-right movement that carried out several attacks against socialist members of parliament. 
The Romanian was arrested on Friday during a police operation in Budapest. 
Police say he was planning a bomb attack on the residence of Hungarian lawmaker Laszlo Esodi. 
(Prima TV, Mediafax, Ziare - 19/05/09)
